The paper deals with extreme multi-label learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with predicting a subset of labels from a large set of possible labels. This falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The paper also mentions the use of ensembles, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with classification and prediction, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
